#  Docker Images and Containers

I learned about Docker images and containers.

Image:
An image is a blueprint used to create containers.

Container:
A running instance of an image.

Commands used:

docker images
- Shows all available images

docker ps -a
- Shows all containers (running and stopped)

docker rm <container_id>
- Removes a container

docker rmi <image_id>
- Removes an image

Learning:
I understood the difference between image and container.
I also learned how to delete containers and images.
